message.content: The possible payload of the initial exploit affecting the victim's bank account could be the file "sdra64.exe" found in the location \Device\HarddiskVolume1\WINDOWS\system32\. This file stands out as it is not a standard Windows system file and could potentially be a malicious executable. Further analysis of this file, its behavior, and any associated network activity would be crucial in determining its role in the suspected keylogging activity.
